  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.openbase.jul.iface.Shutdownable, org.openbase.jul.pattern.Observable<ExceptionReporter.ExceptionReport>

    public class ExceptionReporter
extends org.openbase.jul.pattern.ObservableImpl<ExceptionReporter.ExceptionReport>
    This class can be used to keep track of frequently occurring exceptions. Exceptions are grouped by their type (class) and by the place they occurred (class, method, line number, accessed over the stack trace). Observers can subscribe to be notified when an exception is reported frequently from the same place.
    Author:
    Constantin Romankiewicz

      • report

        public void report(Throwable th)
        Reports an exception. Without a limit given, the default limit is set to -1, meaning that no observers will be notified at any point, except if the limit has already been set before.
        Parameters:
        th - The exception to report.

      • report

        public void report(Throwable th,
                   int limit)
        Reports an exception. If more exceptions are reported from the same place than the limit allows, all observers of this instance will be notified.
        Parameters:
        th - The exception to report.
        limit - How many times this exception may occur from the same place, until observers are notified.
